  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Explore the effects of anti-VEGF targeted drugs on blood pressure and endothelial function in&#xD;
      cancer patients.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Thirty tumor patients with anti-VEGF drugs were selected. Demographic information and&#xD;
      clinical information of all patients were collected before chemotherapy. Ambulatory blood&#xD;
      pressure monitoring and endothelial function measurement (PWV, EndoPAT) were performed.&#xD;
      Ambulatory blood pressure and PWV were reviewed at 2 weeks and 1 month. And EndoPAT, to&#xD;
      evaluate the effects of anti-VEGF drugs on blood pressure and endothelial function in cancer&#xD;
      patients.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
